  "texts": [
    "Upon conducting a series of additional manual assessments, it was noted that many of the ratings provided by ChatGPT were in fact meaningful.",
    "For example, abstracts that received the lowest rating in terms of being 'well-written' or the highest in 'not well-written' were, according to the present author, hard to read due to complex sentence structures, or a frequent use of acronyms/abbreviations.",
    "Another illustrative case was an abstract that exhibited the lowest score on 'replicability'; the present author observed that this abstract lacked a methodology and more closely resembled an essay.",
    "Conversely, some scores assigned by ChatGPT appeared to be somewhat superficial.",
    "An example of this was observed for an abstract that received a high score on 'originality' seemingly because the authors of the abstract had incorporated the words \"We present novel …\"."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}